i.	(3 marks) Analyse these two options using the following ethical frameworks to recommend the right decision: 
From a Deontological point of view, one could claim that the right thing to do would be to fix the vulnerabilities, 
the cons of something severe potentially occurring, far outweighs the benefits of just leaving the matter alone and continuing business as usual. 

ii.	(2 marks) Analyse these two options using the ACM Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct 2018 and recommend the best course of action. 
Many sections of the ACM Code of Ethics could indicate that fixing the vulnerabilities would be the best course of action, such as 1.1: 
Contribute to society and to human well-being, acknowledging that all people are stakeholders in computing. Section 1.5: 
Respect the work required to produce new ideas, inventions, creative works and computing artifacts and section 2: PROFESSIONAL RESPONSIBILITIES.  
